<!-- LI-ION SEGREGATION DIAGRAM -->
<section class="el-sec el-sec-dark">
  <div class="ctr">
    <div class="el-chip">LI-ION COMPLIANCE</div>
    <h2 class="el-h2 el-h2-light">Li-ion battery storage zones — IATA Class 9 watt-hour boundary segregation</h2>
    <p class="el-lede el-lede-light">Lithium-ion batteries are IATA Class 9 dangerous goods with strict watt-hour boundary rules. Devices with batteries under 100 Wh ship as normal cargo with battery markings (UN 3481). Devices with batteries 100-160 Wh require special handling. Anything above 160 Wh is essentially industrial cargo. Our facility maintains physically separated zones with appropriate fire suppression for each tier.</p>
    <div class="el-liion-zones">
      <div class="el-zone-card el-zone-low">
        <div class="el-zone-label">ZONE A · STANDARD</div>
        <div class="el-zone-spec">&lt;100 Wh</div>
        <h3>Smartphones, accessories, small headphones</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Standard rack storage, all levels</li>
          <li>UN 3481 marking on outer cartons</li>
          <li>Standard Nova Poshta Cargo carriage</li>
          <li>Typical battery: 3.6V × 3000-5000 mAh = 11-18 Wh per cell</li>
          <li>Examples: iPhone 15 Pro Max (4685 mAh × 3.85V = 18 Wh), AirPods Pro (~1 Wh)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="el-zone-card el-zone-mid">
        <div class="el-zone-label">ZONE B · MID-CAPACITY</div>
        <div class="el-zone-spec">100-160 Wh</div>
        <h3>Laptops, tablets, mid-tier powerbanks</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Restricted to 2 rack levels maximum</li>
          <li>UN 3480/3481 + Class 9 hazmat label</li>
          <li>Class 9 licensed carrier required for transport</li>
          <li>Typical battery: MacBook Pro 16" = ~100 Wh, iPad Pro 13" = ~40 Wh</li>
          <li>Most laptops fall in this zone — segregated separately from smartphones</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="el-zone-card el-zone-high">
        <div class="el-zone-label">ZONE C · INDUSTRIAL</div>
        <div class="el-zone-spec">&gt;160 Wh</div>
        <h3>Portable power stations, e-bike batteries, large EcoFlow/Bluetti units</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Dedicated isolated zone, dedicated breaker, 3m minimum separation</li>
          <li>Full hazmat documentation per UN 38.3 testing</li>
          <li>Specialized Class 9 carriers only (DHL Hazmat, Schenker, FedEx Premier)</li>
          <li>Typical: EcoFlow DELTA 2 Max = 2048 Wh, Bluetti AC180 = 1152 Wh</li>
          <li>Wartime category — Ukrainian demand for portable power +54% YoY since 2022</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- USE CASES — International brands -->
<section class="el-sec el-sec-light">
  <div class="ctr">
    <div class="el-chip el-chip-dark">USE CASES</div>
    <h2 class="el-h2">Six international electronics brand scenarios we operate in 2026</h2>
    <div class="el-uc-grid">
      <div class="el-uc-card">
        <div class="el-uc-num">🇺🇸 US</div>
        <h3>US premium audio → Comfy, Rozetka</h3>
        <p>US audio brands (audiophile DACs, premium headphones, IEMs) targeting Ukrainian Comfy premium segment and Rozetka. Sea container 30-45 days (cost-efficient, non-perishable), air for high-value SKUs 15-21 days. UDCR registration applies if Bluetooth-enabled. Margin in UA retail typically 35-45% above US DTC pricing.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="el-uc-card">
        <div class="el-uc-num">🇬🇧 UK</div>
        <h3>UK gaming peripherals → Foxtrot, Comfy</h3>
        <p>UK gaming brands (mechanical keyboards, gaming mice, headsets) entering Ukrainian gaming retail. UK-Ukraine FTA = zero import duties. Truck via Bulgaria 8-12 days. ESD-sensitive components (mechanical switches, RGB controllers) — antistatic packaging mandatory. Volume 10-30 pallets/month typical.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="el-uc-card">
        <div class="el-uc-num">🇩🇪 DE</div>
        <h3>German networking → Brain, Citrus, B2B IT</h3>
        <p>German networking brands (routers, switches, mesh systems, NAS) entering Ukrainian B2B IT distribution. EU-Ukraine DCFTA = zero duties on HS 8517. Truck via Poland 5-7 days. ESD-critical for networking PCBs. Volume 15-50 pallets/month for established distributors.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="el-uc-card">
        <div class="el-uc-num">🇨🇳 CN</div>
        <h3>Chinese smart home → Rozetka, Allo</h3>
        <p>Chinese smart home brands (cameras, hubs, smart bulbs, smart plugs) entering Ukrainian smart home retail. Sea via Black Sea 35-50 days. UDCR registration required for WiFi-enabled devices. Volume scales: 20-100+ pallets/month for established brands. Air freight for new product launches (8-15 days).</p>
      </div>
      <div class="el-uc-card">
        <div class="el-uc-num">🇦🇪 AE</div>
        <h3>UAE re-export Apple accessories → Foxtrot, Allo Mobile</h3>
        <p>UAE distributors as re-export hub for premium Apple accessories (MFi-certified cables, cases, audio adapters). Air freight 7-10 days through Boryspil. High AOV per pallet, fast inventory turn. Standard MFN tariffs 0-5%. Antistatic packaging for premium positioning.</p>
