    <div class="el-faq">
      <details><summary>Can a US or German electronics brand sell wholesale into Ukrainian retail without setting up a Ukrainian legal entity?</summary><p>Yes. Cross-border B2B agency model through our Ukrainian operational partner. Your brand remains in home jurisdiction. We are the Ukrainian importer-of-record + retail counterparty. All Ukrainian compliance (VAT, EDI, UDCR IMEI registration) on our side. Monthly USD/EUR settlement to your account.</p></details>
      <details><summary>How does Ukrainian electronics 3PL cost compare to US and EU 3PL?</summary><p>Pallet storage with ESD: $10 Ukraine vs $35-50 US vs $40-65 EU. Pick + IMEI: $0.41 vs $1.20-1.80 US vs $1.80-2.50 EU. Annual 50 pallets + 200 orders/mo: $6-7K Ukraine vs $24-30K US vs $30-40K EU. 3-5x arbitrage driven by labor and real estate costs.</p></details>
      <details><summary>Is rack-level IMEI tracking actually possible in a Ukrainian 3PL?</summary><p>Yes. 4-stage scan: receiving (IMEI→ВМД→HS code), rack slotting (IMEI→shelf location), pick (verification at station), shipping (IMEI→invoice→EDI). 7-year log retention. Generalist UA 3PLs don't do this — we built infrastructure specifically for electronics clients.</p></details>
      <details><summary>What ESD compliance standards does MTP follow?</summary><p>ANSI/ESD S20.20:2021 + ДСТУ IEC 61340-5-1 (Ukrainian = IEC 61340-5-1:2016). Antistatic floor coating, grounded shelving, ESD wrist straps, 40-60% humidity control, antistatic packaging materials. IPC-A-610 Class 2 handling adopted.</p></details>
      <details><summary>How do you handle Li-ion battery storage and shipping compliance?</summary><p>3 zones by watt-hour boundary: <100 Wh standard, 100-160 Wh restricted 2 levels + UN 3480/3481, >160 Wh dedicated isolated zone with full hazmat docs per UN 38.3. Gas-based fire suppression (not water — water damages electronics). Class 9 licensed carriers only for restricted tiers.</p></details>
      <details><summary>What does cross-border transportation cost from US/UK/DE/CN/UAE/TR to Ukraine?</summary><p>US: $2,500-4K sea (30-45 days) or $8-12/kg air. UK: $1.8-2.8K road+sea (10-15) or $5-8/kg air. EU truck: $1.2-2K (5-10 days). China: $2-3.5K sea (35-50). UAE: $1.5-2.8K air (7-10). Turkey: $1-1.8K truck (5-8). Amortizes to $30-80/pallet for transportation.</p></details>
      <details><summary>What is the onboarding timeline?</summary><p>21-30 business days: contract → documentation → international transport → inbound + UDCR → supplier registration → EDI setup → test shipment → production. Complex SKU catalogues (1,000+) or specialized certs — up to 45 days.</p></details>
      <details><summary>How does UDCR (Ukrainian Radio Frequency Center) IMEI registration work?</summary><p>Mandatory since 2009 for imported smartphones/Bluetooth/WiFi devices. Requires Ukrainian importer-of-record. Our operator is importer-of-record. After physical receiving, batch IMEI registered with UDCR within 24h via our partner. Status visible to retailers in UDCR database.</p></details>
      <details><summary>What's the war risk for our electronics inventory in Ukraine?</summary><p>Real consideration. Facilities 35-45km from Kyiv center, outside primary impact zones. Mitigation: war-risk insurance ($0.60-0.80/$100/mo for electronics), 30-day inventory cap, generator backup + blast protection, zero days operational downtime since Feb 2022, government compensation scheme. Most international clients include insurance and operate normally.</p></details>
